def set_up_data(file_path):
    data = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    data = data.drop(index=WHITE_IMAGES, axis=0)
    data = data.drop("Usage", axis=1)
    return data

In [8]:
def get_features(data):
    X = [pixels.split(" ") for pixels in data["pixels"]]
    X = np.array(X)
    X = X.astype("int32")
    X = np.array([image.reshape(48, 48) for image in X])
    return X
In [9]:
def get_labels(data):
    return np.array(data["emotion"])

def get_train_test(X, y, test_size):
    return train_test_split(X, y, test_size=test_size, random_state=42)

In [19]:
def show_pie(distribution):
    mpl.rcParams['font.size'] = 14.0

    _, texts, _ = plt.pie(distribution, labels = CLASS_NAMES, autopct = "%1.1f%%", radius = 2, pctdistance = .85, )
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))

    for text in texts:
        text.set_color("crimson")
    plt.show()

CNN¶

In [24]:
X_train_resh, X_test_resh = X_train.reshape(len(X_train), 48, 48, 1), X_test.reshape(len(X_test), 48, 48, 1)
input_shape = (48, 48, 1)
callback = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='loss', patience=3)
In [25]:
def training_evaluation(history, epochs):
    
    acc = history.history['accuracy']
    val_acc = history.history['val_accuracy']

    loss = history.history['loss']
    val_loss = history.history['val_loss']

    epochs_range = range(epochs)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(epochs_range, acc, label='Training Accuracy')
    plt.plot(epochs_range, val_acc, label='Validation Accuracy')
    plt.legend(loc='lower right')
    plt.title('Training and Validation Accuracy')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(epochs_range, loss, label='Training Loss')
    plt.plot(epochs_range, val_loss, label='Validation Loss')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('Training and Validation Loss')
    plt.show()

Standard model with L2 regularization, 128 nodes¶

In [26]:
tf.random.set_seed(42)
epochs = 10

model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
    layers.Conv2D(32, (4, 4), 
                  activation = "relu", 
                  input_shape = input_shape, 
                  padding = "same", 
                  kernel_regularizer = regularizers.l2(l = 0.01)),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2), padding = "same"),
    layers.Conv2D(64, (6, 6), 
                  activation = "relu", 
                  input_shape = input_shape, 
                  padding = "same",
                  kernel_regularizer = regularizers.l2(l = 0.01)),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2), padding = "same"),
    layers.Flatten(),
    layers.Dense(128, activation = "relu"),
    layers.Dense(len(CLASS_NAMES), activation = "softmax")
    ])

model.compile(optimizer = optimizers.Adam(lr = 0.0001),
             loss = losses.sparse_categorical_crossentropy,
             metrics=['accuracy'])

history = model.fit(X_train_resh, y_train, epochs=epochs, 
                    callbacks = [callback], 
                    validation_data = (X_test_resh, y_test))
